    "extract": "Autoette was an American electric microcar manufactured from the late 1930s to the 1970s. The two-seat, three-wheeled microcar was steered by tiller and powered by batteries from Trojan Battery Co., with motive power provided by a converted 24-volt Dodge 1½ hp. electric starter motor and later a proprietary motor built for Autoette. Models included the \"CruiseAbout\", \"Golfmobile\" and \"Electric Truck\"."
